&lt;p&gt;Band 6 Specialist Practitioner (Nurse or Physiotherapist)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 WTE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in the Chest Clinic at University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust to work within a small team of Respiratory Specialist nurses. Working throughout the trust with predominantly  COPD and Asthma patients, assessing, implementing, evaluating and making recommendations for care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Initiates Rapid Support Discharge in liaison with community teams and acts as an expert resource for patients and staff with these conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enquiries to Sister Claire Young 01752 439949 or Inreach team bleep on 81926. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
